{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2bc75a87-e7e0-4226-be23-44465c43b395","content":"I don't have a skill for **analyzing** crash dumps — the available `dump-collect` skill is only for **capturing** them, not post-mortem debugging.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows, most powerful)\n   - Open the `.dmp`, load SOS: `.loadby sos coreclr`\n   - `!pe` — print exception\n   - `!clrstack` — managed stack\n   - `!analyze -v` — automatic crash analysis\n\n3. **Visual Studio** (Windows)\n   - File → Open → File → select the `.dmp`\n   - Click \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n\n### Quick Start\n\nIf you have `dotnet-dump` available on this machine and can provide the dump file path, I can help you run the analysis interactively. Want to try that?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2bb04dd3-8060-4a8e-90a2-ff3e65438982","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me look at the available skills to see if any can help with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\n\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files. I should provide guidance on how to analyze a .dmp file instead.","outputTokens":524,"requestId":"DA08:1287AC:7233C59:7AE825B:6A03DA17"},"id":"ca9ad5a5-4595-47e1-98c0-dbde5f7252ca","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:55:50.182Z","parentId":"2332b0ee-ae28-4853-b094-613111f13209"}
